24:55.400 --> 24:58.360
to speak with Dr. Charlotte Laughlin and Dr. William Crider.

24:58.900 --> 25:01.460
Dr. Laughlin has done research for a biography of Howard,

25:01.800 --> 25:05.260
and Dr. Crider teaches science fiction and fantasy at Howard Payne University.

25:05.940 --> 25:08.360
Dr. Crider explains what a pastiche is.

25:09.340 --> 25:11.400
Well, in the sense that we've been talking about it,

25:11.400 --> 25:15.220
it's where one writer takes a character and a world

25:16.080 --> 25:19.120
like the Hiborian Age created by another writer

25:19.120 --> 25:24.160
and writes new stories with the same character and the same setting.

25:24.720 --> 25:27.800
And he gets the full credit for the story,

25:27.880 --> 25:32.920
but the other writer has created the character and the historical setting.

25:34.000 --> 25:40.320
Also, De Camp did something similar where he took incomplete Howard stories

25:40.320 --> 25:45.440
and changed them into Conan stories,

25:45.440 --> 25:49.240
which would be a pastiche of a slightly different kind,

25:49.480 --> 25:52.780
but it's the same principle operating.

26:01.720 --> 26:04.800
The biography of Howard, entitled Dark Valley Destiny,

26:05.320 --> 26:07.840
has been written by L. Sprague De Camp and his wife, Catherine,

26:08.020 --> 26:10.340
and will probably be out sometime in the next year.

26:10.760 --> 26:13.320
The book will mainly be a psychological study of Howard,

26:13.320 --> 26:16.480
which attempts to explain why he wrote the kind of material he did.

26:16.920 --> 26:21.300
Conan has been so popular that a major movie about him, entitled Conan the Barbarian,

26:21.740 --> 26:23.420
is premiering this week across the country.

26:23.980 --> 26:27.700
It was filmed in Spain by director John Milius and produced by Dino de Laurentiis,

26:28.020 --> 26:30.420
and has muscle man Arnold Schwarzenegger playing Conan.

26:30.940 --> 26:35.360
Early reports indicate that it does a marvelous job of conveying the atmosphere of sword and sorcery,

26:35.440 --> 26:36.800
essential to a Conan adventure.

26:37.300 --> 26:40.340
Laughlin and Crider talk about the movie and about Conan's popularity.

26:41.140 --> 26:46.700
If this is a huge success, like Star Wars, let's say,

26:47.080 --> 26:50.380
that could give even more impetus to this kind of thing,

26:50.440 --> 26:57.280
and we may see Howard going on forever with these pastiches being done by...

26:57.280 --> 27:00.140
I think it's possible that they would be continued,

27:00.360 --> 27:03.940
because the original idea was to fill out Conan's life,

27:04.560 --> 27:07.580
you know, have his life completely covered by the pastiches from,

27:07.580 --> 27:11.820
I don't know if it went to his boyhood, but certainly all of his adult life

27:11.820 --> 27:15.640
when he was an old King Conan, and it's already gone beyond that.

27:15.840 --> 27:19.740
They filled out his life, and then they're going back to, you know, this stage in his life.

27:19.860 --> 27:20.680
He did such and such.

27:21.560 --> 27:25.440
So certainly they're not going to stop with what would be the chronological life of Conan,

27:25.700 --> 27:27.980
so the potential to go on beyond is there.

27:28.920 --> 27:32.580
The potential to keep Conan alive and adventuring is definitely there.

27:32.880 --> 27:34.920
We should be hearing a lot more from Conan.

